Upcountry: Living or situated remote from the seacoast; as, an upcountry residence.

Unkiss: To cancel or annul what was done or sealed by a kiss; to cancel by a kiss.
Universe of discourse: everything which may be considered, explicitly or implicitly, in a particular theory or discussion.
Ukase: In Russia, a published proclamation or imperial order, having the force of law.
Uprightness: the quality or state of being upright.
Unripeness: Quality or state of being unripe.
Uncompromising: Not admitting of compromise; making no truce or concessions; obstinate; unyielding; inflexible.
Unigeniture: The state of being the only begotten.
Unappealable: Not appealable; that can not be carried to a higher tribunal by appeal; as, an unappealable suit or action.
Urochordal: Of or pertaining to the Urochorda.
Udal: Allodial; -- a term used in Finland, Shetland, and Orkney. See Allodial.
Unreserved: Not reserved; not kept back; not withheld in part; unrestrained.
Unanimity: The quality or state of being unanimous.
Unipara: A woman who has borne one child.
Underbid: To bid less than, as when a contract or service is offered to the lowest bidder; to offer to contract, sell, or do for a lower price than.
Ultramundane: Being beyond the world, or beyond the limits of our system.
Unsling: To take off the slings of, as a yard, a cask, or the like; to release from the slings.
Undergrowth: That which grows under trees; specifically, shrubs or small trees growing among large trees.
Unswell: To sink from a swollen state; to subside.
Unprelated: Deposed from the office of prelate.
Unpriced: Not priced; being without a fixed or certain value; also, priceless.
Unwarrantable: Not warrantable; indefensible; not vindicable; not justifiable; illegal; unjust; improper.
Urosternite: The sternal, or under piece, of any one of the uromeres of insects and other arthropods.
Urechitoxin: A poisonous glucoside found accompanying urechitin, and extracted as a bitter white crystalline substance.
Underbrush: Shrubs, small trees, and the like, in a wood or forest, growing beneath large trees; undergrowth.
Unpromise: To revoke or annul, as a promise.
Unsuccessful: Not successful; not producing the desired event; not fortunate; meeting with, or resulting in, failure; unlucky; unhappy.
Ungular: Of or pertaining to a hoof, claw, or talon; ungual.
Underget: To get under or beneath; also, to understand.
Umlauted: Having the umlaut; as, umlauted vowels.
underlock: A lock of wool hanging under the belly of a sheep.
Unreadiness: The quality or state of being unready.
Usbegs: A Turkish tribe which about the close of the 15th century conquered, and settled in, that part of Asia now called Turkestan.
Uranous: Pertaining to, or containing, uranium; designating those compounds in which uranium has a lower valence as contrasted with the uranic compounds.
Upspurner: A spurner or contemner; a despiser; a scoffer.
Upbear: To bear up; to raise aloft; to support in an elevated situation; to sustain.
Umbel: A kind of flower cluster in which the flower stalks radiate from a common point, as in the carrot and milkweed. It is simple or compound; in the latter case, each peduncle bears another little umbel, called umbellet, or umbellule.
Unatonable: Not capable of being brought into harmony; irreconcilable.
Urbicol\u00e6: An extensive family of butterflies, including those known as skippers (Hesperiadæ).
Univalent: Having a valence of one; capable of combining with, or of being substituted for, one atom of hydrogen; monovalent; -- said of certain atoms and radicals.
Underbearer: One who supports or sustains; especially, at a funeral, one of those who bear the corpse, as distinguished from a bearer, or pallbearer, who helps to hold up the pall.
Utes: An extensive tribe of North American Indians of the Shoshone stock, inhabiting Colorado, Utah, New Mexico, Arizona, and adjacent regions. They are subdivided into several subordinate tribes, some of which are among the most degraded of North American Indians.
Umber: To color with umber; to shade or darken; as, to umber over one's face.
Unboot: To take off the boots from.
Untitled: Not titled; having no title, or appellation of dignity or distinction.
Unbounded: Having no bound or limit; as, unbounded space; an, unbounded ambition.
Undulatory: Moving in the manner of undulations, or waves; resembling the motion of waves, which successively rise or swell rise or swell and fall; pertaining to a propagated alternating motion, similar to that of waves.
Unswaddle: To take a swaddle from; to unswathe.
Unnun: To remove from condition of being a nun.
Unlade: To take the load from; to take out the cargo of; as, to unlade a ship or a wagon.
Underprop: To prop from beneath; to put a prop under; to support; to uphold.
Uglily: In an ugly manner; with deformity.
Unadvised: Not prudent; not discreet; ill advised.
Unconformable: Not conformable; not agreeable; not conforming.
Undecagon: A figure having eleven angles and eleven sides.
Ultraviolet: Lying outside the visible spectrum at its blue-violet end; -- said of light more refrangible (i. e. having a shorter wavelength) than the extreme violet rays of the visible spectrum.  Electromagnetic radiation with wavelengths shorter than those of ultrviolet light are not usually considered as light waves, but are classified differently.  The ultraviolet region of the electromagnetic spectrum is generally considered as comprising those electromagnetic emissions with wavelengths lying between those of visible light and those of X-rays, i. e. between 4000 Angstroms and 100 Angstroms.
Unwit: Want of wit or understanding; ignorance.
Urite: One of the segments of the abdomen or post-abdomen of arthropods.
Undeniable: Not deniable; incapable of denial; palpably true; indisputable; obvious; as, undeniable evidence.
Unsincerity: The quality or state of being unsincere or impure; insincerity.
Unmiter: To deprive of a miter; to depose or degrade from the rank of a bishop.
Unmanned: Deprived of manly qualities; deficient in vigor, strength, courage, etc.; weak; effeminate.
Uproot: To root up; to tear up by the roots, or as if by the roots; to remove utterly; to eradicate; to extirpate.
Un-Romanized: Not subjected to Roman arms or customs.
Unwariness: The quality or state of being unwary; carelessness; heedlessness.
Uliginose: Muddy; oozy; slimy; also, growing in muddy places.
Unbespeak: To unsay; hence, to annul or cancel.
Urceolus: Any urn-shaped organ of a plant.
Unmuzzle: To loose from a muzzle; to remove a muzzle from.
umlaut: The euphonic modification of a root vowel sound by the influence of a, u, or especially i, in the syllable which formerly followed.
Unprotestantize: To render other than Protestant; to cause to change from Protestantism to some other form of religion; to deprive of some Protestant feature or characteristic.
Unfix: To loosen from a fastening; to detach from anything that holds; to unsettle; as, to unfix a bayonet; to unfix the mind or affections.
Unbeliever: One who does not believe; an incredulous person; a doubter; a skeptic.
Unpaved: Not paved; not furnished with a pavement.
Unctuous: Of the nature or quality of an unguent or ointment; fatty; oily; greasy.
Urocerata: A division of boring Hymenoptera, including Tremex and allied genera. See Illust. of Horntail.
Ungod: To deprive of divinity; to undeify.
Upcast: To cast or throw up; to turn upward.
Unbear: To remove or loose the bearing rein of (a horse).
Ulna: The postaxial bone of the forearm, or brachium, corresponding to the fibula of the hind limb. See Radius.
Underwood: Small trees and bushes that grow among large trees; coppice; underbrush; -- formerly used in the plural.
Unseel: To open, as the eyes of a hawk that have been seeled; hence, to give light to; to enlighten.
Unnumbered: Not numbered; not counted or estimated; innumerable.
Umbilication: A slight, navel-like depression, or dimpling, of the center of a rounded body; as, the umbilication of a smallpox vesicle; also, the condition of being umbilicated.
Unprejudiced: Not prejudiced; free from undue bias or prepossession; not preoccupied by opinion; impartial; as, an unprejudiced mind; an unprejudiced judge.
Ure: To use; to exercise; to inure; to accustom by practice.
Ultramontanism: The principles of those within the Roman Catholic Church who maintain extreme views favoring the pope's supremacy; -- so used by those living north of the Alps in reference to the Italians; -- rarely used in an opposite sense, as referring to the views of those living north of the Alps and opposed to the papal claims.  Cf. Gallicanism.
Urn: To inclose in, or as in, an urn; to inurn.
Unmoralized: Not restrained or tutored by morality.
Uncapper: An instrument for removing an exploded cap from a cartridge shell.
Unfathered: Having no father; fatherless; hence, born contrary to nature.
Urticate: To sting with, or as with, nettles; to irritate; to annoy.
Unchristened: Not christened; as, an unchristened child.
Upstairs: Being above stairs; as, an upstairs room.
Untruism: Something not true; a false statement.
Urinogenital: Pertaining to the urinary and genital organs; genitourinary; urogenital; as, the urinogenital canal.
Unfavorable: Not favorable; not propitious; adverse; contrary; discouraging.
Undergrove: A grove of shrubs or low trees under taller ones.
Unmold: To change the form of; to reduce from any form.
Under-arm: Done (as bowling) with the arm not raised above the elbow, that is, not swung far out from the body; underhand.  Cf. Over-arm and Round-Arm.
Uncap: To remove a cap or cover from.
Unacquaintance: The quality or state of being unacquainted; want of acquaintance; ignorance.
Unregenerate: Not regenerated; not renewed in heart; remaining or being at enmity with God.
Untalked: Not talked; not mentioned; -- often with of.
Urinator: One who dives under water in search of something, as for pearls; a diver.
Ungird: To loose the girdle or band of; to unbind; to unload.
Unresty: Causing unrest; disquieting; as, unresty sorrows.
Upstart: Suddenly raised to prominence or consequence.
Unlimited: Not limited; having no bounds; boundless; as, an unlimited expanse of ocean.
Ursuline: Of or pertaining to St. Ursula, or the order of Ursulines; as, the Ursuline nuns.
Unisonant: Being in unison; having the same degree of gravity or acuteness; sounded alike in pitch.
Upstare: To stare or stand upward; hence, to be uplifted or conspicuous.
Underniceness: A want of niceness; indelicacy; impropriety.
Unlove: To cease to love; to hate.
Urostyle: A styliform process forming the posterior extremity of the vertebral column in some fishes and amphibians.
Urtication: The act or process of whipping or stinging with nettles; -- sometimes used in the treatment of paralysis.
Ultimate: To come or bring to an end or issue; to eventuate; to end.
Unqueen: To divest of the rank or authority of queen.
Urbane: Courteous in manners; polite; refined; elegant.
Undulated: Resembling, or in the nature of, waves; having a wavy surface; undulatory.
Unguis: The nail, claw, talon, or hoof of a finger, toe, or other appendage.
Unbegot: Not begot; not yet generated; also, having never been generated; self-existent; eternal.
Unshot: Not hit by a shot; also, not discharged or fired off.
Urinate: To discharge urine; to make water.
Underhung: Resting on a track at the bottom, instead of being suspended; -- said of a sliding door.
Uplandish: Of or pertaining to uplands; dwelling on high lands.
Unanswered: Not answered; not replied to; as, an unanswered letter.
Unflesh: To deprive of flesh; to reduce a skeleton.
Umbonate: Having a conical or rounded projection or protuberance, like a boss.
Unwrap: To open or undo, as what is wrapped or folded.
Ultima: The last syllable of a word.
Underrate: A price less than the value; as, to sell a thing at an underrate.
Unhelm: To deprive of the helm or helmet.
Ultimo: In the month immediately preceding the present; as, on the 1st ultimo; -- usually abbreviated to ult.  Cf. Proximo.
Ululate: To howl, as a dog or a wolf; to wail; as, ululating jackals.
Unhallowed: Not consecrated; hence, profane; unholy; impious; wicked.
Unsecret: Not secret; not close; not trusty; indiscreet.
Uncombine: To separate, as substances in combination; to release from combination or union.
Umbo: The boss of a shield, at or near the middle, and usually projecting, sometimes in a sharp spike.
Urohyal: Of or pertaining to one or more median and posterior elements in the hyoidean arch of fishes.
Undecyl: The radical regarded as characteristic of undecylic acid.
Unworthy: Not worthy; wanting merit, value, or fitness; undeserving; worthless; unbecoming; -- often with of.
Unquiet: Not quiet; restless; uneasy; agitated; disturbed.
Uncipher: To decipher; as, to uncipher a letter.
Upridged: Raised up in a ridge or ridges; as, a billow upridged.
Undeeded: Not deeded or transferred by deed; as, undeeded land.
Uprighteously: In an upright or just manner.
Umbles: The entrails and coarser parts of a deer; hence, sometimes, entrails, in general.
Undulate: To move in, or have, undulations or waves; to vibrate; to wave; as, undulating air.
Uprush: Act of rushing upward; an upbreak or upburst; as, an uprush of lava.
Unlorded: Deprived of the rank of a lord.
Unstick: To release, as one thing stuck to another.
Undergird: To bind below; to gird round the bottom.
Untwain: To rend in twain; to tear in two.
Uphold: To hold up; to lift on high; to elevate.
Undercliff: A subordinate cliff on a shore, consisting of material that has fallen from the higher cliff above.
Utilitarianism: The doctrine that the greatest happiness of the greatest number should be the end and aim of all social and political institutions.
Unburrow: To force from a burrow; to unearth.
Unconformability: The quality or state of being unconformable; unconformableness.
Uranoscopy: Observation of the heavens or heavenly bodies.
Uroxanic: Pertaining to, or designating, an acid, C5H8N4O6, which is obtained, as a white crystalline substance, by the slow oxidation of uric acid in alkaline solution.
Urethane: A white crystalline substance, NH2.CO.OC2H5, produced by the action of ammonia on ethyl carbonate or by heating urea nitrate and ethyl alcohol. It is used as a hypnotic, antipyretic, and antispasmodic. Hence, any ester of carbamic acid.
Unseasonable: Not seasonable; being, done, or occurring out of the proper season; ill-timed; untimely; too early or too late; as, he called at an unseasonable hour; unseasonable advice; unseasonable frosts; unseasonable food.
Underpoise: To weigh, estimate, or rate below desert; to undervalue.
Unplight: To unfold; to lay open; to explain.
Unguent: A lubricant or salve for sores, burns, or the like; an ointment.
Uncage: To loose, or release, from, or as from, a cage.
Unitary: Of or pertaining to a unit or units; relating to unity; as, the unitary method in arithmetic.
Unnerve: To deprive of nerve, force, or strength; to weaken; to enfeeble; as, to unnerve the arm.
Unfledged: Not fledged; not feathered; hence, not fully developed; immature.
Umbratious: Suspicious; captious; disposed to take umbrage.
Unallied: Not allied; having no ally; having no connection or relation; as, unallied species or genera.
Unbashful: Not bashful or modest; bold; impudent; shameless.
Utilitarian: One who holds the doctrine of utilitarianism.
Uniocular: Of, pertaining to, or seated in, one eye; monocular.
Unguinous: Consisting of, or resembling, fat or oil; oily; unctuous; oleaginous.
Unsoldiered: Not equipped like a soldier; unsoldierlike.
Unbreast: To disclose, or lay open; to unbosom.
Unbosom: To disclose freely; to reveal in confidence, as secrets; to confess; -- often used reflexively; as, to unbosom one's self.
Undaunted: Not daunted; not subdued or depressed by fear.
Undergrown: Of small stature; not grown to a full height or size.
Ungrateful: Not grateful; not thankful for favors; making no returns, or making ill return for kindness, attention, etc.; ingrateful.
Unlike: Not like; dissimilar; diverse; having no resemblance; as, the cases are unlike.
Unsex: To deprive of sex, or of qualities becoming to one's sex; esp., to make unfeminine in character, manners, duties, or the like; as, to unsex a woman.
Unifacial: Having but one front surface; as, some foliaceous corals are unifacial, the polyp mouths being confined to one surface.
Umbilicate: Depressed in the middle, like a navel, as a flower, fruit, or leaf; navel-shaped; having an umbilicus; as, an umbilicated smallpox vesicle.
Unsew: To undo, as something sewn, or something inclosed by sewing; to rip apart; to take out the stitches of.
Urostege: One of the plates on the under side of the tail of a serpent.
Underreckon: To reckon below what is right or proper; to underrate.
Urethroplasty: An operation for the repair of an injury or a defect in the walls of the urethra.
Uranitic: Of or pertaining to uranium; containing uranium.
Underproduction: The production of less than is demanded or of less than the usual supply.
Unoriginated: Not originated; existing from all eternity.
Ubiquity: Existence everywhere, or in all places, at the same time; omnipresence; as, the ubiquity of God is not disputed by those who admit his existence.
Unsheathe: To deprive of a sheath; to draw from the sheath or scabbard, as a sword.
Ularburong: A large East Indian nocturnal tree snake (Dipsas dendrophila). It is not venomous.
Ugliness: The quality or state of being ugly.
Underproportioned: Of inadequate or inferior proportions; small; poor.
Unpraise: To withhold praise from; to deprive of praise.
Unfriendship: The state or quality of being unfriendly; unfriendliness; enmity.
Umbilical: Of or pertaining to an umbilicus, or umbilical cord; umbilic.
Uvitic: Pertaining to, or designating, an acid, CH3C6H3(CO2H)2, obtained as a white crystalline substance by the partial oxidation of mesitylene; -- called also mesitic acid.
Ulnare: One of the bones or cartilages of the carpus, which articulates with the ulna and corresponds to the cuneiform in man.
Unanswerable: Not answerable; irrefutable; conclusive; decisive; as, he gave an unanswerable argument.
Unappalled: Not appalled; not frightened; dauntless; undaunted.
Ultimatum: A final proposition, concession, or condition; especially, the final propositions, conditions, or terms, offered by either of the parties in a diplomatic negotiation; the most favorable terms that a negotiator can offer, the rejection of which usually puts an end to the hesitation.
Undertaking: The act of one who undertakes, or engages in, any project or business.
Unaccountability: The quality or state of being unaccountable.
Urochrome: A yellow urinary pigment, considered by Thudichum as the only pigment present in normal urine. It is regarded by Maly as identical with urobilin.
Ulmaceous: Of or pertaining to a suborder of urticaceous plants, of which the elm is the type.
Ural-Altaic: Of or pertaining to the Urals and the Altai; as the Ural-Altaic, or Turanian, languages.
Upsetting thermometer: A thermometer by merely inverting which the temperature may be registered. The column of mercury is broken and, as it remains until the instrument is reset, the reading may be made at leisure.
Untold: Not told; not related; not revealed; as, untold secrets.
University extension: The extension of the advantages of university{3} instruction by means of lectures and classes at various centers.
Unaccountable: Not accountable or responsible; free from control.
Umble pie: A pie made of umbles. See To eat humble pie, under Humble.
Unfurl: To loose from a furled state; to unfold; to expand; to open or spread; as, to unfurl sails; to unfurl a flag.
Unguestlike: In a manner not becoming to a guest.
Uratic: Of or containing urates; as, uratic calculi.
Unharness: To strip of harness; to loose from harness or gear; as, to unharness horses or oxen.
Urim: A part or decoration of the breastplate of the high priest among the ancient Jews, by which Jehovah revealed his will on certain occasions. Its nature has been the subject of conflicting conjectures.
Upokororo: An edible fresh-water New Zealand fish (Prototroctes oxyrhynchus) of the family Haplochitonidæ. In general appearance and habits, it resembles the northern lake whitefishes and trout. Called also grayling.
Uncloister: To release from a cloister, or from confinement or seclusion; to set free; to liberate.
Uric: Of or pertaining to urine; obtained from urine; as, uric acid.
Upstroke: An upward stroke, especially the stroke, or line, made by a writing instrument when moving upward, or from the body of the writer, or a line corresponding to the part of a letter thus made.
Unnest: To eject from a nest; to unnestle.
Underyoke: To subject to the yoke; to make subject.
Unslacked: Not slacked; unslaked; as, unslacked lime.
Uncomeatable: Not to be come at, or reached; inaccessible.
Unstitch: To open by picking out stitches; to take out, or undo, the stitches of; as, to unstitch a seam.
Underdealing: Crafty, unfair, or underhand dealing; unfair practice; trickery.
Undergo: To go or move below or under.
Ureal: Of or pertaining to urea; containing, or consisting of, urea; as, ureal deposits.
Unbeast: To deliver from the form or nature of a beast.
Uncurse: To free from a curse or an execration.
Untighten: To make less tight or tense; to loosen.
Urceolate: Shaped like a pitcher or urn; swelling below, and contracted at the orifice, as a calyx or corolla.
Uncastle: To take a castle from; to turn out of a castle.
Univariant: Having one degree of freedom or variability.
Ustion: The act of burning, or the state of being burned.
Unstudied: Not studied; not acquired by study; unlabored; natural.
Underbuy: To buy at less than the real value or worth; to buy cheaper than.
Unsheriff: To depose from the office of sheriff.
Unwrinkle: To reduce from a wrinkled state; to smooth.
Ultra vires: Beyond power; transcending authority; -- a phrase used frequently in relation to acts or enactments by corporations in excess of their chartered or statutory rights.
Undersay: To say by way of derogation or contradiction.
Unnail: To remove the nails from; to unfasten by removing nails.
Underchamberlain: A deputy chamberlain of the exchequer.
Unreserve: Absence of reverse; frankness; freedom of communication.
Utilize: To make useful; to turn to profitable account or use; to make use of; as, to utilize the whole power of a machine; to utilize one's opportunities.
Unspar: To take the spars, stakes, or bars from.
Unarmed: Not armed or armored; having no arms or weapons.
Urochord: The central axis or cord in the tail of larval ascidians and of certain adult tunicates.
Unembodied: Free from a corporeal body; disembodied; as, unembodied spirits.
Urocele: A morbid swelling of the scrotum due to extravasation of urine into it.
Useless: Having, or being of, no use; unserviceable; producing no good end; answering no valuable purpose; not advancing the end proposed; unprofitable; ineffectual; as, a useless garment; useless pity.
Unchariot: To throw out of a chariot.
Unlovely: Not lovely; not amiable; possessing qualities that excite dislike; disagreeable; displeasing; unpleasant.
Unwilling: Not willing; loath; disinclined; reluctant; as, an unwilling servant.
Ulnar: Of or pertaining to the ulna, or the elbow; as, the ulnar nerve.
Unspike: To remove a spike from, as from the vent of a cannon.
Upblow: To blow up; as, the wind upblows from the sea.
Upstreet: Toward the higher part of a street; as, to walk upstreet.
Unloader: One who, or that which, unloads; a device for unloading, as hay from a wagon.
Uplander: One dwelling in the upland; hence, a countryman; a rustic.
Upbreak: A breaking upward or bursting forth; an upburst.
Urubu: The black vulture (Catharista atrata). It ranges from the Southern United States to South America. See Vulture.
Unparliamentary: Not parliamentary; contrary to the practice of parliamentary bodies.
Unapparel: To divest of clothing; to strip.
Unread: Not read or perused; as, an unread book.
Up-to-date: Extending to the present time; having style, manners, knowledge, or other qualities that are abreast of the times.
Unjust: Acting contrary to the standard of right; not animated or controlled by justice; false; dishonest; as, an unjust man or judge.
Urinometry: The estimation of the specific gravity of urine by the urinometer.
Unguiculata: An extensive division of Mammalia including those having claws or nails, as distinguished from the hoofed animals (Ungulata).
Unguiculate: Furnished with nails, claws, or hooks; clawed. See the Note under Nail, n., 1.
Undersoil: The soil beneath the surface; understratum; subsoil.
Undying: Not dying; imperishable; unending; immortal; as, the undying souls of men.
Unfeeling: Destitute of feeling; void of sensibility; insensible; insensate.
Unclog: To disencumber of a clog, or of difficulties and obstructions; to free from encumbrances; to set at liberty.
Uncurtain: To remove a curtain from; to reveal.
Uniter: One who, or that which, unites.
Universalness: The quality or state of being universal; universality.
Uncleansable: Incapable of being cleansed or cleaned.
Urosacral: Of or pertaining to both the caudal and sacral parts of the vertebral column; as, the urosacral vertebræ of birds.
Urobilin: A yellow pigment identical with hydrobilirubin, abundant in the highly colored urine of fever, and also present in normal urine. See Urochrome.
Unsound: Not sound; not whole; not solid; defective; infirm; diseased.
Underbrace: To brace, fasten, or bind underneath or below.
Undecane: A liquid hydrocarbon, C11H24, of the methane series, found in petroleum; -- so called from its containing eleven carbon atoms in the molecule.
Urethroscopy: Examination of the urethra by means of the urethroscope.
Unparadise: To deprive of happiness like that of paradise; to render unhappy.
Unmade: Not yet made or formed; as, an unmade grave.
Unlive: To &unr_;&unr_;ve in a contrary manner, as a life; to live in a manner contrary to.
Unbed: To raise or rouse from bed.
Uncomfortable: Feeling discomfort; uneasy; as, to be uncomfortable on account of one's position.
Ultraist: One who pushes a principle or measure to extremes; an extremist; a radical; an ultra.
Undeceive: To cause to be no longer deceived; to free from deception, fraud, fallacy, or mistake.
Unfruitful: Not producing fruit or offspring; unproductive; infertile; barren; sterile; as, an unfruitful tree or animal; unfruitful soil; an unfruitful life or effort.
Uraniscoraphy: Suture of the palate. See Staphyloraphy.
Unlucky: Not lucky; not successful; unfortunate; ill-fated; unhappy; as, an unlucky man; an unlucky adventure; an unlucky throw of dice; an unlucky game.
Urosome: The abdomen, or post-abdomen, of arthropods.
Underdo: To do less thoroughly than is requisite; specifically, to cook insufficiently; as, to underdo the meat; -- opposed to overdo.
Unicornous: Having but a single horn; -- said of certain insects.
Unencumber: To free from incumbrance; to disencumber.
Undeterminate: Nor determinate; not settled or certain; indeterminate.
Uncheckable: Not capable of being checked or stopped.
Ulva: A genus of thin papery bright green seaweeds including the kinds called sea lettuce.
Unpucker: To smooth away the puckers or wrinkles of.
Ulcerate: To affect with, or as with, an ulcer or ulcers.
Ulexite: A mineral occurring in white rounded crystalline masses. It is a hydrous borate of lime and soda.
Upholsterer: One who provides hangings, coverings, cushions, curtains, and the like; one who upholsters.
Underfellow: An underling; a mean, low fellow.
Uncrown: To deprive of a crown; to take the crown from; hence, to discrown; to dethrone.
Unbe: To cause not to be; to cause to be another.
Ubiquist: One of a school of Lutheran divines which held that the body of Christ is present everywhere, and especially in the eucharist, in virtue of his omnipresence.  Called also ubiquitist, and ubiquitary.
Underfurnish: To supply with less than enough; to furnish insufficiently.
Unclose: To open; to separate the parts of; as, to unclose a letter; to unclose one's eyes.
Unchancy: Happening at a bad time; unseasonable; inconvenient.
Unloose: To become unfastened; to lose all connection or union.
Unzoned: Not zoned; not bound with a girdle; as, an unzoned bosom.
Unappropriate: To take from private possession; to restore to the possession or right of all; as, to unappropriate a monopoly.
Underaction: Subordinate action; a minor action incidental or subsidiary to the main story; an episode.
Unbelief: The withholding of belief; doubt; incredulity; skepticism.
Unsweat: To relieve from perspiration; to ease or cool after exercise or toil.
Ungeld: A person so far out of the protection of the law, that if he were murdered, no geld, or fine, should be paid, or composition made by him that killed him.

Unpaint: To remove the paint from; to efface, as a painting.
Unacceptability: The quality of being unacceptable; unacceptableness.
umhofo: An African two-horned rhinoceros (Atelodus simus or Rhinoceros simus); -- called also chukuru, and white rhinoceros.
Unawares: Without design or preparation; suddenly; without premeditation, unexpectedly.
Unexperienced: Not experienced; being without experience; inexperienced.
Unicapsular: Having but one capsule to each flower.

Urceole: A vessel for water for washing the hands; also, one to hold wine or water.

Undertenant: The tenant of a tenant; one who holds lands or tenements of a tenant or lessee.

Unmerchantable: Not merchantable; not fit for market; being of a kind, quality, or quantity that is unsalable.
Universalian: Of or pertaining to Universalism; Universalist.

Unpope: To divest of the character, office, or authority of a pope.

Uxorial: Dotingly fond of, or servilely submissive to, a wife; uxorious; also, becoming a wife; pertaining to a wife.
Unbody: To leave the body; to be disembodied; -- said of the soul or spirit.
Uriniferous: Bearing or conveying urine; as, uriniferous tubules.
Utriculus: A little sac, or bag; a utricle; especially, a part of the membranous labyrinth of the ear. See the Note under Ear.
Unnotify: To retract or withdraw a notice of.
Upholstery: The articles or goods supplied by upholsterers; the business or work of an upholsterer.
Upgather: To gather up; to contract; to draw together.
Uretic: Of or pertaining to the urine; diuretic; urinary; as, uretic medicine.
Undoubted: Not doubted; not called in question; indubitable; indisputable; as, undoubted proof; undoubted hero.
Unget: To cause to be unbegotten or unborn, or as if unbegotten or unborn.
Usager: One who has the use of anything in trust for another.
Unfeigned: Not feigned; not counterfeit; not hypocritical; real; sincere; genuine; as, unfeigned piety; unfeigned love to man.
Underbelly: The lower ventral part of the abdomen of an animal, especially one that walks on four feet.

Ursal: The ursine seal. See the Note under 1st Seal.
Unaneled: Not aneled; not having received extreme unction.
Unobservance: Want or neglect of observance; inobservance.
Unrobe: To disrobe; to undress; to take off the robes.

Unwormed: Not wormed; not having had the worm, or lytta, under the tongue cut out; -- said of a dog.
Uncustomable: Not customable, or subject to customs duties.
Undertaker: One who undertakes; one who engages in any project or business.
Ungodly: Not godly; not having regard for God; disobedient to God; wicked; impious; sinful.
Uncanny: Not canny; unsafe; strange; weird; ghostly.
Ungentle: Not gentle; lacking good breeding or delicacy; harsh.
Uncling: To cease from clinging or adhering.
Uneasiness: The quality or state of being uneasy; restlessness; disquietude; anxiety.
Underfong: To undertake; to take in hand; to receive.
Understudy: One who studies another's part with a view to assuming it in an emergency.
Umbecast: To cast about; to consider; to ponder.
Unmeet: Not meet or fit; not proper; unbecoming; unsuitable; -- usually followed by for.
Unchastity: The quality or state of being unchaste; lewdness; incontinence.

Uphand: Lifted by the hand, or by both hands; as, the uphand sledge.
Unhandy: Clumsy; awkward; as, an Unhandy man.
Unbacked: Never mounted by a rider; unbroken.
Unshipment: The act of unshipping, or the state of being unshipped; displacement.

Unconsecrate: To render not sacred; to deprive of sanctity; to desecrate.
Unimproved: Not improved; not made better or wiser; not advanced in knowledge, manners, or excellence.
Unknot: To free from knots; to untie.
Undifferentiated: Not differentiated; specifically (Biol.), homogenous, or nearly so; -- said especially of young or embryonic tissues which have not yet undergone differentiation (see Differentiation, 3), that is, which show no visible separation into their different structural parts.
unhoard: To take or steal from a hoard; to pilfer.
Unlawed: Not having the claws and balls of the forefeet cut off; -- said of dogs.
Undersleeve: A sleeve of an under-garment; a sleeve worn under another,
Unprevented: Not prevented or hindered; as, unprevented sorrows.
Unsadden: To relieve from sadness; to cheer.
Utilization: The act of utilizing, or the state of being utilized.
Unexceptive: Not exceptive; not including, admitting, or being, an exception.
Unmartyr: To degrade from the rank of a martyr.
Uncreatedness: The quality or state of being uncreated.
Unifollilate: Having only one leaflet, as the leaves of the orange tree.
Umbellifer: A plant producing an umbel or umbels.
Unquestioned: Not called in question; not doubted.
Unipolar: Having, or acting by means of, one pole only.
Unfoldment: The acct of unfolding, or the state of being unfolded.
Unguentary: Like an unguent, or partaking of its qualities.
Unfounded: Not founded; not built or established.
Unbewitch: To free from a spell; to disenchant.
Unicity: The condition of being united; quality of the unique; unification.
Uncentury: To remove from its actual century.
Unbowed: Not bent or arched; not bowed down.
Unhoop: To strip or deprive of hoops; to take away the hoops of.
Unbowel: To deprive of the entrails; to disembowel.
Unhook: To loose from a hook; to undo or open by loosening or unfastening the hooks of; as, to unhook a fish; to unhook a dress.

Unsymmetrical: Wanting in symmetry, or due proportion pf parts.

Unpray: To revoke or annul by prayer, as something previously prayed for.

Uralian: Of or relating to the Ural Mountains.
Unvoweled: Having no vowel sounds or signs.
Umbellularia: A genus of deep-sea alcyonaria consisting of a cluster of large flowerlike polyps situated at the summit of a long, slender stem which stands upright in the mud, supported by a bulbous base.
Udaler: In the Shetland and Orkney Islands, one who holds property by udal, or allodial, right.

Unravel: To become unraveled, in any sense.

Undevil: To free from possession by a devil or evil spirit; to exorcise.
Upturn: To turn up; to direct upward; to throw up; as, to upturn the ground in plowing.
Undershot: Having the lower incisor teeth projecting beyond the upper ones, as in the bulldog.
Underthing: Something that is inferior and of little worth.
Utia: Any species of large West Indian rodents of the genus Capromys, or Utia. In general appearance and habits they resemble rats, but they are as large as rabbits.
Unequal: Not equal; not matched; not of the same size, length, breadth, quantity, strength, talents, acquirements, age, station, or the like; as, the fingers are of unequal length; peers and commoners are unequal in rank.

Unlay: To untwist; as, to unlay a rope.
Ultion: The act of taking vengeance; revenge.

Unveracity: Want of veracity; untruthfulness; as, unveracity of heart.
Ungraceful: Not graceful; not marked with ease and dignity; deficient in beauty and elegance; inelegant; awkward; as, ungraceful manners; ungraceful speech.
Unequity: Want of equity or uprightness; injustice; wickedness; iniquity.
Underdig: To dig under or beneath; to undermine.
Uromere: Any one of the abdominal segments of an arthropod.

In addition, however, they held that Judas and the murderers of Christ were saved.  So called from the founder of the sect, Ucke Wallis, a native of Friesland.
Unpastor: To cause to be no longer pastor; to deprive of pastorship.
Upside-down: having the part normally pointed upward pointed downward; inverted.
Ureide: Any one of the many complex derivatives of urea; thus, hydantoin, and, in an extended dense, guanidine, caffeine, et., are ureides.
Unhasp: To unloose the hasp of; to unclose.
Unalist: An ecclesiastic who holds but one benefice; -- distinguished from pluralist.
Upheave: To heave or lift up from beneath; to raise.
Unbegilt: Not gilded; hence, not rewarded with gold.
Urnful: As much as an urn will hold; enough to fill an urn.
Undecennary: Occurring once in every period of eleven years; undecennial.
Unthinking: Not thinking; not heedful; thoughtless; inconsiderate; as, unthinking youth.
Unfellowed: Being without a fellow; unmatched; unmated.
Uchees: A tribe of North American Indians belonging to the Creek confederation.
Upsilon: The 20th letter (Υ, υ) of the Greek alphabet, a vowel having originally the sound of &oomacr_; as in room, becoming before the 4th century b. c. that French u or Ger. ü. Its equivalent in English is u or y.
Unrelenting: Not relenting; unyielding; rigid; hard; stern; cruel.
Uniquity: The quality or state of being unique; uniqueness.
Unition: The act of uniting, or the state of being united; junction.
Unsaint: To deprive of saintship; to deny sanctity to.
Uncover: To take off the hat or cap; to bare the head in token of respect.
Undercraft: A sly trick or device; as, an undercraft of authors.
Ullmannite: A brittle mineral of a steel-gray color and metallic luster, containing antimony, arsenic, sulphur, and nickel.
Unseal: To break or remove the seal of; to open, as what is sealed; as, to unseal a letter.
Unseam: To open the seam or seams of; to rip; to cut; to cut open.
Unclutch: To open, as something closely shut.
Unslaked: Not slaked; unslacked; as, an unslaked thirst; unslaked lime.
Un-: An inseparable prefix, or particle, signifying not; in-; non-. In- is prefixed mostly to words of Latin origin, or else to words formed by Latin suffixes; un- is of much wider application, and is attached at will to almost any adjective, or participle used adjectively, or adverb, from which it may be desired to form a corresponding negative adjective or adverb, and is also, but less freely, prefixed to nouns. Upgrowth: The process or result of growing up; progress; development.
Undertaxed: Taxed too little, or at a lower rate than others.
Uredospore: The thin-walled summer spore which is produced during the so-called Uredo stage of certain rusts. See (in the Supplement) Uredinales, Heterœcious, etc.
Underhand: By secret means; in a clandestine manner; hence, by fraud; unfairly; dishonorably.
Unthriftiness: The quality or state or being unthrifty; profuseness; lavishness.
Underhang: To hang under or down; to suspend.
Untrunked: Separated from its trunk or stock.
Underheave: To heave or lift from below.
Unceasable: Not capable of being ended; unceasing.
Unplat: To take out the folds or twists of, as something previously platted; to unfold; to unwreathe.
Uvic: Pertaining to, or obtained from, grapes; specifically, designating an organic acid, C7H8O3 (also called pyrotritartaric acid), obtained as a white crystalline substance by the decomposition of tartaric and pyrotartaric acids.
Unwieldy: Not easily wielded or carried; unmanageable; bulky; ponderous.
Unsting: To disarm of a sting; to remove the sting of.
Uncowl: To divest or deprive of a cowl.
Unfeudalize: To free from feudal customs or character; to make not feudal.
Untune: To make incapable of harmony, or of harmonious action; to put out of tune.
up-to-the-minute: being the most recent available; completely up-to-date
Undersong: The burden of a song; the chorus; the refrain.
Unspecialized: Not specialized; specifically (Biol.), not adapted, or set apart, for any particular purpose or function; as, an unspecialized unicellular organism.
Unsolder: To separate or disunite, as what has been soldered; hence, to divide; to sunder.
Unfellow: To prevent from being a fellow or companion; to separate from one's fellows; to dissever.
Unwell: Not well; indisposed; not in good health; somewhat ill; ailing.
Unchristianness: The quality or state of being unchristian.
Usurp: To commit forcible seizure of place, power, functions, or the like, without right; to commit unjust encroachments; to be, or act as, a usurper.
Unnecessity: The state of being unnecessary; something unnecessary.
Ubiquitariness: Quality or state of being ubiquitary, or ubiquitous.
Uncircumcision: The absence or want of circumcision.
Unnecessary: Not necessary; not required under the circumstances; unless; needless; as, unnecessary labor, care, or rigor.
Unlord: To deprive of the rank or position of a lord.
Unborrowed: Not borrowed; being one's own; native; original.
Unconditioned: Not conditioned or subject to conditions; unconditional.
Uninterested: Not interested; not having any interest or property in; having nothing at stake; as, to be uninterested in any business.
Ungka: The siamang; -- called also ungka ape.
Unconstitutional: Not constitutional; not according to, or consistent with, the terms of a constitution of government; contrary to the constitution; as, an unconstitutional law, or act of an officer.
Uncloud: To free from clouds; to unvail; to clear from obscurity, gloom, sorrow, or the like.
Utilizable: Capable of being utilized; as, the utilizable products of the gas works.
Umbelliferone: A tasteless white crystalline substance, C9H6O3, found in the bark of a certain plant (Daphne Mezereum), and also obtained by the distillation of certain gums from the Umbelliferæ, as galbanum, asafetida, etc.  It is analogous to coumarin.  Called also hydroxy-coumarin.  Its strong fluorescence under ultraviolet light makes it useful in analytical biochemistry, as, for exmple, to detect phosphatase activity by hydrolysis of umbelliferyl phosphate.
Unpaganize: To cause to cease to be pagan; to divest of pagan character.
Unscience: Want of science or knowledge; ignorance.
Unknit: To undo or unravel what is knitted together.
Ungrave: To raise or remove from the grave; to disinter; to untomb; to exhume.
Unfile: To remove from a file or record.
Unsecularize: To cause to become not secular; to detach from secular things; to alienate from the world.
Ungka-puti: The agile gibbon; -- called also ungka-pati, and ungka-etam. See Gibbon.
Unfaithful: Not faithful; not observant of promises, vows, allegiance, or duty; violating trust or confidence; treacherous; perfidious; as, an unfaithful subject; an unfaithful agent or servant.
Unwork: To undo or destroy, as work previously done.
Underplot: A series of events in a play, proceeding collaterally with the main story, and subservient to it.
Uranyl: The radical UO2, conveniently regarded as a residue of many uranium compounds.
Unionistic: Of or pertaining to union or unionists; tending to promote or preserve union.
Unpervert: To free from perversion; to deliver from being perverted; to reconvert.
Uniterable: Not iterable; incapable of being repeated.
Unconfound: To free from a state of confusion, or of being confounded.
Undershapen: Under the usual shape or size; small; dwarfish.
Universalistic: Of or pertaining to the whole; universal.
Underside: The lower or lowest side of anything.
Unsacrament: To deprive of sacramental character or efficacy; as, to unsacrament the rite of baptism.
Unhide: To bring out from concealment; to discover.
Unshale: To strip the shale, or husk, from; to uncover.
Undercharge: A charge that is less than is usual or suitable.
Unblindfold: To free from that which blindfolds.
Unidimensional: Having but one dimension. See Dimension.
Unlearned: Not learned; untaught; uneducated; ignorant; illiterate.
Unliquored: Not moistened or wet with liquor; dry.
Unorganized: Not organized; being without organic structure; specifically (Biol.), not having the different tissues and organs characteristic of living organisms, nor the power of growth and development; as, the unorganized ferments. See the Note under Ferment, n., 1.
Unparagoned: Having no paragon or equal; matchless; peerless.
Undight: To put off; to lay aside, as a garment.
Unreverence: Absence or lack of reverence; irreverence.
Unblind: To free from blindness; to give or restore sight to; to open the eyes of.
Unfrequented: Rarely visited; seldom or never resorted to by human beings; as, an unfrequented place or forest.
Unciform: The unciform bone. See Illust. of Perissodactyla.
Undreamed: Not dreamed, or dreamed of; not th&unr_;ught of; not imagined; -- often followed by of.
Unblemished: Not blemished; pure; spotless; as, an unblemished reputation or life.
Unify: To cause to be one; to make into a unit; to unite; to view as one.
Uranite: A general term for the uranium phosphates, autunite, or lime uranite, and torbernite, or copper uranite.
Uplean: To lean or incline upon anything.
Undertone: A low or subdued tone or utterance; a tone less loud than usual.
Undershrieve: A low shrub; a woody plant of low stature.
-uret: A suffix with the same meaning as -ide. See -ide.
Unheard: Not heard; not perceived by the ear; as, words unheard by those present.
Undress: A loose, negligent dress; ordinary dress, as distinguished from full dress.
Unequalness: The quality or state of being unequal; inequality; unevenness.
Ultramontane: One who resides beyond the mountains, especially beyond the Alps; a foreigner.
Unwitch: To free from a witch or witches; to fee from witchcraft.
Unheart: To cause to lose heart; to dishearten.
Unearth: To drive or draw from the earth; hence, to uncover; to bring out from concealment; to bring to light; to disclose; as, to unearth a secret.
Unexceptionable: Not liable to any exception or objection; unobjectionable; faultless; good; excellent; as, a man of most unexceptionable character.
Uninfringible: That may not be infringed; as, an uninfringible monopoly.
Unassented: Not assented; -- said specif. of stocks or bonds the holders of which refuse to deposit them by way of assent to an agreement altering their status, as in a readjustment.

Ur\u00e6us: A serpent, or serpent's head and neck, represented on the front of the headdresses of divinities and sovereigns as an emblem of supreme power.
Unimuscular: Having only one adductor muscle, and one muscular impression on each valve, as the oyster; monomyarian.

Unwedgeable: Not to be split with wedges.
Undated: Not dated; having no date; of unknown age; as, an undated letter.
Uniphonous: Having but one sound, as the drum.
Utensil: That which is used; an instrument; an implement; especially, an instrument or vessel used in a kitchen, or in domestic and farming business.
Underdrain: To drain by forming an underdrain or underdrains in; as, to underdrain land.

Uncity: To deprive of the rank or rights of a city.
Underfringe: A lower fringe; a fringe underneath something.
unconscious: Usually the unconscious; that part of the mind in which mental processes occur that are not accesible to the awareness, but may significantly influence behavior.
Unsin: To deprive of sinfulness, as a sin; to make sinless.
Undoing: The reversal of what has been done.
Unexpected: Not expected; coming without warning; sudden.
Undoer: One who undoes anything; especially, one who ruins another.
Ureter: The duct which conveys the urine from the kidney to the bladder or cloaca. There are two ureters, one for each kidney.
Undeserver: One of no merit; one who is nor deserving or worthy.
Uvular: Of or pertaining to a uvula.
Unbreech: To remove the breeches of; to divest or strip of breeches.
Unreformation: Want of reformation; state of being unreformed.
Unprecedented: Having no precedent or example; not preceded by a like case; not having the authority of prior example; novel; new; unexampled.
underage: Shortage or deficiency in amount; shortfall.
Ulceration: The process of forming an ulcer, or of becoming ulcerous; the state of being ulcerated; also, an ulcer.
Unsafety: The quality or state of being in peril; absence of safety; insecurity.
Uranology: A discourse or treatise on the heavens and the heavenly bodies; the study of the heavens; uranography.
Uranoplasty: The plastic operation for closing a fissure in the hard palate.
Universe: All created things viewed as constituting one system or whole; the whole body of things, or of phenomena; the to~ pa^n of the Greeks, the mundus of the Latins; the world; creation.
Undulating: Rising and falling like waves; resembling wave form or motion; undulatory; rolling; wavy; as, an undulating medium; undulating ground.
Up-train: A train going in the direction of the metropolis or the main terminus.
Useful: Full of use, advantage, or profit; producing, or having power to produce, good; serviceable for any end or object; helpful toward advancing any purpose; beneficial; profitable; advantageous; as, vessels and instruments useful in a family; books useful for improvement; useful knowledge; useful arts.

Unworship: Lack of worship or respect; dishonor.
Ungainliness: The state or quality of being ungainly; awkwardness.
Unlash: To loose, as that which is lashed or tied down.

Untuck: To unfold or undo, as a tuck; to release from a tuck or fold.
Unbecoming: Not becoming; unsuitable; unfit; indecorous; improper.
Unitable: Capable of union by growth or otherwise.
Understanding: The act of one who understands a thing, in any sense of the verb; knowledge; discernment; comprehension; interpretation; explanation.
Underback: A vessel which receives the wort as it flows from the mashing tub.
Uppricked: Upraised; erect; -- said of the ears of an animal.
Unnear: Not near; not close to; at a distance from.
Unbrewed: Not made by brewing; unmixed; pure; genuine.
Unsucceedable: Not able or likely to succeed.
Unshroud: To remove the shroud from; to uncover.
Unearned: Not earned; not gained by labor or service.
Unfaith: Absence or want of faith; faithlessness; distrust; unbelief.
Undertenancy: Tenancy or tenure under a tenant or lessee; the tenure of an undertenant.
Unform: To decompose, or resolve into parts; to destroy the form of; to unmake.
Unabsorbable: Not absorbable; specifically (Physiol.), not capable of absorption; unable to pass by osmosis into the circulating blood; as, the unabsorbable portion of food.

Unpolicied: Not having civil polity, or a regular form of government.
Ungracious: Not gracious; showing no grace or kindness; being without good will; unfeeling.
Unappropriated: Not specially appropriate; having no special application.
Undistinctive: Making no distinctions; not discriminating; impartial.
Underwrite: To practice the business of insuring; to take a risk of insurance on a vessel or the like.
Understander: One who understands, or knows by experience.
Uncloak: To remove, or take off, one's cloak.
Untile: To take the tiles from; to uncover by removing the tiles.
Undergraduateship: The position or condition of an undergraduate.
Unigenous: Being of one kind; being of the same genus.
Undercroft: A subterranean room of any kind; esp., one under a church (see Crypt), or one used as a chapel or for any sacred purpose.

Ungear: To strip of gear; to unharness; to throw out of gear.
Unifilar: Having only one thread; involving the use of only one thread, wire, fiber, or the like; as, unifilar suspension.
Undermeal: The inferior, or after, part of the day; the afternoon.
Univalence: The quality or state of being univalent.
Uniparous: Producing but one egg or young at a time.
Undine: One of a class of fabled female water spirits who might receive a human soul by intermarrying with a mortal.
Urinarium: A reservoir for urine, etc., for manure.

Unbraid: To separate the strands of; to undo, as a braid; to unravel; to disentangle.

Unedge: To deprive of the edge; to blunt.
Uzema: A Burman measure of twelve miles.
Unspilt: Not spilt or wasted; not shed.
Understandingly: In an understanding manner; intelligibly; with full knowledge or comprehension; intelligently; as, to vote upon a question understandingly; to act or judge understandingly.
Undergraduate: Of or pertaining to an undergraduate, or the body of undergraduates.
Unprop: To remove a prop or props from; to deprive of support.
Usefulness: The quality or state of being useful; utility; serviceableness; advantage.
Unvalued: Not valued; not appraised; hence, not considered; disregarded; valueless; as, an unvalued estate.
Upheaval: The act of upheaving, or the state of being upheaved; esp., an elevation of a portion of the earth's crust.
Uranometry: A chart or catalogue of fixed stars, especially of stars visible to the naked eye.
Ultimately: As a final consequence; at last; in the end; as, afflictions often tend to correct immoral habits, and ultimately prove blessings.
Ungain: Ungainly; clumsy; awkward; also, troublesome; inconvenient.
underlying: Lying under or beneath; as, the underlying strata of a locality.
Unruffled: Not ruffled or agitated; smooth; calm; tranquil; quiet.
ullet: A European owl (Syrnium aluco) of a tawny color; -- called also uluia.
Unbend: To cease to be bent; to become straight or relaxed.
Underwhelm: To interest less than anticipated; to be dull to (a person).
Uncovenanted: Not covenanted; not granted or entered into under a covenant, agreement, or contract.
Ungive: To yield; to relax; to give way.
Unbind: To remove a band from; to set free from shackles or fastenings; to untie; to unfasten; to loose; as, unbind your fillets; to unbind a prisoner's arms; to unbind a load.
Unmortise: To loosen, unfix, or separate, as things mortised together.

Unfailing: Not failing; not liable to fail; inexhaustible; certain; sure.
Unitive: Having the power of uniting; causing, or tending to produce, union.

Unbenevolence: Absence or want of benevolence; ill will.
Unquestionable: Not questionable; as, an unquestionable title.
Unfolder: One who, or that which, unfolds.
Uphilt: To thrust in up to the hilt; as, to uphilt one's sword into an enemy.
Untraded: Not dealt with in trade; not visited for purposes of trade.
Unseemliness: The quality or state of being unseemly; unbecomingness.
Uxoricidal: Of or pertaining to uxoricide; tending to uxoricide.
Unthinker: A person who does not think, or does not think wisely.
Underlay: The inclination of a vein, fault, or lode from the vertical; a hade; -- called also underlie.

Unitarian: Of or pertaining to Unitarians, or their doctrines.
Unreality: The quality or state of being unreal; want of reality.
Usnic: Pertaining to, or designating, a complex acid obtained, as a yellow crystalline substance, from certain genera of lichens  (Usnea, Parmelia, etc.).
Unkingship: The quality or condition of being unkinged; abolition of monarchy.
Underground: Beneath the surface of the earth.
Uniflorous: Bearing one flower only; as, a uniflorous peduncle.
Untempter: One who does not tempt, or is not a tempter.
Uniaxial: Having but one optic axis, or line of no double refraction.

Ut: The first note in Guido's musical scale, now usually superseded by do. See Solmization.
Up: Inclining up; tending or going up; upward; as, an up look; an up grade; the up train.
Us: The persons speaking, regarded as an object; ourselves; -- the objective case of we. See We.
Urn-shaped: Having the shape of an urn; as, the urn-shaped capsules of some mosses.
Ungenerous: Not generous; illiberal; ignoble; unkind; dishonorable.

Underload: to load (a truck, etc.) with less than its full capacity; -- in certain circumstances, an inefficient use of resources.
Universal grammar: the principles forming the basis for the human ability to understand language.

Unused: Not used; as, an unused book; an unused apartment.
Unfilial: Unsuitable to a son or a daughter; undutiful; not becoming a child.

Uprouse: To rouse up; to rouse from sleep; to awake; to arouse.
Ultra-: A prefix from the Latin ultra beyond (see Ulterior), having in composition the signification beyond, on the other side, chiefly when joined with words expressing relations of place; as, ultramarine, ultramontane, ultramundane, ultratropical, etc. In other relations it has the sense of excessively, exceedingly, beyond what is common, natural, right, or proper; as, ultraconservative; ultrademocratic, ultradespotic, ultraliberal, ultraradical, etc.
Understand: To have the use of the intellectual faculties; to be an intelligent being.
Unrein: To loosen the reins of; to remove restraint from.
Unreaved: Not torn, split, or parted; not torn to pieces.
Upend: To end up; to set on end, as a cask.
U: the twenty-first letter of the English alphabet, is a cursive form of the letter V, with which it was formerly used interchangeably, both letters being then used both as vowels and consonants. U and V are now, however, differentiated, U being used only as a vowel or semivowel, and V only as a consonant. The true primary vowel sound of U, in Anglo-Saxon, was the sound which it still retains in most of the languages of Europe, that of long oo, as in tool, and short oo, as in wood, answering to the French ou in tour. Etymologically U is most closely related to o, y (vowel), w, and v; as in two, duet, dyad, twice; top, tuft; sop, sup; auspice, aviary. See V, also O and Y.
Unluckiness: Quality or state of being unlucky.

Underline: To mark a line below, as words; to underscore.
Underling: An inferior person or agent; a subordinate; a low-ranking employee.
